LYNCHBURG COLLEGE
48223
HERBARIUM

Flora of Virginia
*Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brum.
near Sherando, Augusta Co.

(Handwritten text begins)
Colony of 20 plants scattered for 20 ft.
along S facing bank of Drebank Creek in 
hardwoods with *Brachyelytrum*, *Osmunda cinnamomea*,
*Tsuga* & *Lygodium*. 150 ft. S of Coal Road
& .3 mi. W of its junction with Rt #664.
(Sherando Quad.)
Charles E. Stevens
No. 20, 191                                el. 1580 ft.
                                                Aug. 29, 1987
(Handwritten text ends)

copyright reserved


*Galax urceolata*
